{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.7",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 7 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:1",
      "text": "“Has not man a hard service upon earth, and are not his days like the days of a hireling?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:2",
      "text": "Like a slave who longs for the shadow, and like a hireling who looks for his wages,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:3",
      "text": "so I am allotted months of emptiness, and nights of misery are apportioned to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:4",
      "text": "When I lie down I say, ‘When shall I arise?’ But the night is long, and I am full of tossing till the dawn.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:5",
      "text": "My flesh is clothed with worms and dirt; my skin hardens, then breaks out afresh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:6",
      "text": "My days are swifter than a weaver's shuttle, and come to their end without hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:7",
      "text": "“Remember that my life is a breath; my eye will never again see good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:8",
      "text": "The eye of him who sees me will behold me no more; while thy eyes are upon me, I shall be gone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:9",
      "text": "As the cloud fades and vanishes, so he who goes down to Sheol does not come up;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:10",
      "text": "he returns no more to his house, nor does his place know him any more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:11",
      "text": "“Therefore I will not restrain my mouth; I will speak in the anguish of my spirit; I will complain in the bitterness of my soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:12",
      "text": "Am I the sea, or a sea monster, that thou settest a guard over me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:13",
      "text": "When I say, ‘My bed will comfort me, my couch will ease my complaint,’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:14",
      "text": "then thou dost scare me with dreams and terrify me with visions,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:15",
      "text": "so that I would choose strangling and death rather than my bones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:16",
      "text": "I loathe my life; I would not live for ever. Let me alone, for my days are a breath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:17",
      "text": "What is man, that thou dost make so much of him, and that thou dost set thy mind upon him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:18",
      "text": "dost visit him every morning, and test him every moment?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:19",
      "text": "How long wilt thou not look away from me, nor let me alone till I swallow my spittle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:20",
      "text": "If I sin, what do I do to thee, thou watcher of men? Why hast thou made me thy mark? Why have I become a burden to thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.7.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 7:21",
      "text": "Why dost thou not pardon my transgression and take away my iniquity? For now I shall lie in the earth; thou wilt seek me, but I shall not be.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
